properties.publicTransport: Buses will be diverting from their usual routes, no stops will be missed. Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
The Cahill Expressway southbound (lanes 7 and 8 of the Sydney Harbour Bridge) will be closed at High St and Mount St, Kirribilli from 9pm Sunday 26 December 2021 to 4.30am Monday 10 January 2022.

Lane 6 on the Sydney Harbour Bridge will also close each night from 9pm to 5.30am. One southbound lane will remain open during this time.

Motorists can detour via the Sydney Harbour Tunnel in both directions or detour via the city using the Grosvenor St off-ramp.

The Cahill Expressway northbound lanes will also be closed for major events between 10pm 30 December and 4am 7 January.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on the Sydney Harbour Bridge and Harbour Tunnel during the closure period so allow extra travel time.
properties.diversions: Sydney Harbour Tunnel or Sydney Harbour Bridge via Grosvenor St off-ramp continue via Grosvenor St, Bridge St and Macquarie St to join the Eastern Distributor at Shakespeare Place.
